name: methylmalonate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase (CoA-acylating)
classes: Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: 2-methyl-3-oxopropanoate + CoA + H2O + NAD+ = propanoyl-CoA + HCO3- + NADH [RN:R00922]
comment: Also converts 3-oxopropanoate into acetyl-CoA [3]. The reaction occurs in two steps with the decarboxylation process preceding CoA-binding [3]. Bicarbonate rather than CO2 is released as a final product [3].
